<Author>freekicker
<Content>Forget it or else they forget you This is actually a very nice and modern hotel in Siemensstadt, an industrial suburb of Berlin.. A benefit is the nearby metro station Rohrdamm (20 min to downtown) and the location just a few miles for Tegel airport, which is served by a hotel-owned shuttle. Rooms are large, bright and colourful and the quality of food in the restaurant is above average.. I also liked the sauna  pool area, which I enjoyed almost alone one afternoon (large pool, 2 saunas, enough beds for relaxing, fitness tools and fitness bar.At my arrival in the morning I was asked to fill in the reception forms, but then the check in procedure was postponed to 2 pm. On returning I took my luggage out of the locker, was handed over my key 鈥?again no special check in or welcome procedure, although I expected to get some breakfast/dinner vouchers etc. 鈥淭he restaurant know all鈥?was the receptionist鈥檚 answer, when I asked for the coupons.In the room I read about the group鈥檚 individualized pillow offer and, intending to comfortably watching a soccer game, asked housekeeping around 6 pm by phone for pillow #5. It arrived after the end of the game, shortly after 8 pm. At least she was not disturbed in watching her game. In the breakfast rooms with a large selection of cold and warm food and top quality fruit juices, they advertised for fresh made pancakes. I ordered one portion with maple sirup, showed my seat 鈥? And was completely forgotten. No, not completely. The same guy next morning remembered me (鈥淵ou are the guest who ordered pancakes yesterday !?鈥? and this time it worked. True not the ideal delivery behaviour to the visitor of the Berlin Logistics Convention 鈥?br/>On check-out the inevitable happened. They did not know anything about my vouchers, attempted to charge the dinner (included in my package price) to me and only gave up after consulting to more management levels, although I had the original reservation for with all details and benefits with me all the time.Let鈥檚 not forget the departure. The shuttle started with 2 people (a young lady and me) and a mass of luggage, but just 2 min before arriving at the airport the driver was told that he forgot 3 people at the hotel, obviously distracted by the beautiful lady at his side 鈥︹€?br/>Forget them at HI or else they forget you ! 
