<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great location, great service We drove into Berlin last August (2002), having beenunable to visit Dresden because of the flooding. Found this Holiday Innon a beautiful quiet street in Spandau (northwest suburb). The staffwere extremely helpful, spokeexcellent English, and tolerated my German. They helped us witheverything fromfinding a self-service laundromat to calling the Deutsch Auto Club toget us a flood-free route back to Prague for our flight home. Our roomwas definitely at the top end of the Holiday Inn scale. Breakfastbuffets (included) were bountiful; one could choose amomg American style(bacon, sausage, scrambled eggs, etc.) or German style (boiled eggs,rolls, jams, cheeses, cold cuts, etc.). Their indoor-outdoor Trattoriaserved very good dishes just right for late night suppers.The hotel iswithin three easy walking blocks through a very quiet, safe neighborhoodto the Rohrdamm U-bahn (subway) station, from which there is easy accesstoall parts of Berlin. 
